  <title>Fantastic actor spotted at QAGOMA</title>
  <content>
A FANTASTIC Four actor has been spotted playing tourist at the Queensland Gallery of Modern Art's Marvel exhibition.
Ioan Gruffudd, a camera hanging around his neck, was snapped at QAGOMA over the weekend, while browsing the Marvel: Creating the Cinematic Universe exhibit.
The Welsh actor will star in new ABC crime drama series Harrow in Brisbane this month. Rehearsals are under way.
It is believed Gruffudd flew into Brisbane about three weeks ago and has been in full tourist mode around the city, including dining at restaurants in Fortitude Valley and Woolloongabba.
Gruffudd was last in Queensland to film San Andreas in 2014.
Harrow is the latest project from Brisbane production company Hoodlum Entertainment.
